      "text": "As the weather warms up, adventure calls—but so does the need for safety! This week, Yuma and Tucson Air Branch crews sprang into action.\n\nIn Yuma County, a mountain biker was rescued after a serious fall on Sugarloaf Trail.\n\nNear Tucson, a lost hiker was found and airlifted out of the Catalina Mountains just in time.\n\nHeading outdoors? Don’t forget to hydrate, plan ahead, and stay safe—our teams are ready, but prevention is always best! \n\n#YumaAirBranch #TucsonAirBranch #BORSTAR #StaySafe #RescueReady",
